53/https://www.nst.com.my/news/nation/2020/02/562769/2-new-2019-ncov-cases-2-malaysians-who-returned-wuhan|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> He was discharged from the hospital on 18 February.<ref name=\"father and son recovered and discharged from hospital\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/02/18/father-son-who-tested-positive-for-covid-19-discharged-and-free-to-go-home|title=Father, son who tested positive for Covid-19, discharged and free to go home|last=Kaos Jr|first=Joseph|work=The Star|date=18 February 2020|accessdate=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318022029/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/02/18/father-son-who-tested-positive-for-covid-19-discharged-and-free-to-go-home|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| Discharged\n|-\n| 12\n| G4\n| 5 February 2020\n| 18 February 2020\n| 9\n| {{MYS}}\n| A Malaysian male national from Wuhan who returned to Malaysia after the evacuation operation on 4 February. He did not show any symptoms during the physical examination procedures at KLIA. Subsequent testing on a quarantine centre in Nilai of Negeri Sembilan revealed that he and his father were positive for the new coronavirus. They were then being referred to an isolation ward at Tuanku Ja'afar Hospital in Seremban for further treatment.<ref name=\"2 COVID from evacuation\"/> He was discharged from the hospital on 18 February.<ref name=\"father and son recovered and discharged from hospital\"/>\n| Discharged\n|-\n| 13\n| G3\n| 5 February 2020\n| 22 February 2020\n| 40\n| {{MYS}}\n| A Malaysian female national who recently visited by her infected brother (the 9th patient) in [[Kedah]]'s [[Sungai Petani]] during [[Chinese New Year]] on 23 January. She later developed symptoms of fever, throat pain and cough where she went to a private clinic for treatment.<ref name=\"13th and 14th infected patient\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/02/07/coronavirus-